{
  "stem": "19895.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I wanted to be a decent Hungarian boy who happened to be Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I had the same aspirations as everybody else.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my Father lost his business.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many of our friends had similar situations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So our life became very limited as far as providing for our daily needs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But somehow, we survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Father always found some innovative ways of doing some business and some work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he had a job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When Father lost his business, and this which I earlier mentioned, the-- the merchandising of hats were further limited.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had a job.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were attendance of an apartment building.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But strangely, that was also by law taken away, because an attendant of the apartment building, the one who collects the rents, one who is maintaining the building, one who calls the plumbers or the repairman for the owner of the apartment building, that was somewhat of a job of somebody who knows everything in the building, and what goes on.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And again, Jews were not permitted to continue in that position at the very end of these days leading up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So when we had to leave that and had to find a new apartment and move away, again, we have had very difficult days of how to maintain our daily needs.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I recall the city of Budapest didn't have enough hotels.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we still had a fairly nice apartment, where we could give up one room and give it out like bed and breakfast.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And father went down to the railroad station and-- and had some people in small hotels around the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If they didn't have rooms, then they were able to direct them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And Father met them and took them to our apartment for bed and breakfast.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
